        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 4:41PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 441 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Paris Landing State Park, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Paris, Paris Landing State Park, Springville, Big Sandy, Haigler
Ridge, Sunnyside, Conyersville, Pine Hill, Old Springville, Buchanan,
India, and Big Sandy Unit Tennessee National Wildlife Refuge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for west
Tennessee.</instruction>
